Title: An Act Regarding Lobster Measurement
Official Title: An Act Regarding Lobster Measurement
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1790
H.P. 1201 House of Representatives, April 24, 2025
Reference to the Committee on Marine Resources suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative FAULKINGHAM of Winter Harbor.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §6431, sub-§1-B, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 512, §2, is amended
3 to read:
4 1-B. Compliance with interstate fishery management plan. The commissioner may
5 adopt rules to set minimum and maximum lobster sizes different from those specified in
6 subsection 1 when When necessary to comply with changes to the Atlantic States Marine
7 Fisheries Commission Interstate Fishery Management Plan for American Lobster regarding
8 minimum and maximum lobster sizes different from those specified in subsection 1, the
9 commissioner shall submit legislation to the Legislature with proposed minimum and
10 maximum lobster sizes. Rules adopted pursuant to this subsection are routine technical
11 rules as defined in Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2‑A. The commissioner shall notify the
12 joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over marine resources
13 matters when initiating rulemaking pursuant to this subsection.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This bill removes the authority of the Commissioner of Marine Resources to adopt
1166 rules to set minimum and maximum lobster sizes different from those specified in statute.
1177 Instead, the bill requires the department to submit legislation to the Legislature when
1188 changes to minimum and maximum lobster sizes are necessary to comply with changes to
1199 the Atlantic States Marine Fisheries Commission Interstate Fishery Management Plan for
2200 American Lobster.
